^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I had several kibs ask me why I bid 2@S rather than one 1@S. My bid of 2@S is basically a weak 2. Since I have an opening weak 2 bid, I have a 2@S overcall as well. That is my usual criteria. Let me give you a quick explanation of my weak 2 style. There are some people who put restrictions on weak 2s, such as not opening with an outside 4 card major, or not opening with a void. I personally open any 5-10 point hand with a six card suit as a weak 2, regardless of other holdings.  I think the weak 2 is a disruptive bid, and so I like to open it with any excuse. |
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Further, I understand the restriction about 4 card majors, even though I don't agree. In my experience, even if you have a 4-4 fit, the hand usually plays better or at least as well in the six card suit. But, I really don't understand the restriction about having a void. It seems to me the void gives you more reason to open a weak 2, not less. After all said, you have to decide what style suits you best as many experts like to put restrictions on weak 2s.|
