^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me answer the question regarding what I open with 4/4 in the minors. I told a kib before that 1@D is what I tend to open, but I think I need to reconsider that answer.  I tend to open 1@C actually, because it keeps the bidding lower, unless my diamonds are way better than my clubs. However, many people play that you open 1@D with 4-4 in the minors. And I have been told on good authority that the standard is to open 1@D with 4-4 in the minors.  The problem I have with opening 1@D and then bidding 2C, such as 1D-1S-2C, is I would assume partner has 5 diamonds. So, I am not sure I agree with the standard approach. The reason I am not positive about this is because, since I usually play a weak NT, I would open the hand 1N, and there would be no problem.|
