^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|OK, now as to the question about whether sandy should open. Here is my philosophy on that, many of you have heard this before. I tend to like to play rule of 20 openers in all 4 seats. And sandy does not have a rule of 20 opener. I will explain why I play that in a minute. But let me first discuss why many people would open sandy's hand in 3rd seat. They play something known as "the rule of 15", which says if your high card points and # of spades total 15, then you should open in 3rd (and perhaps 4th) seat. sandy's hand does meet the rule of 15. The idea behind the rule of 15 is if you own the spade suit, you can compete effectively. Let us play the hand.|
