^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I have had many questions from the kibitzers on whether East should have opened. So, let me discuss light openers in general.  20 years ago, experts did not use the rule of 20 to open in first and second seat. They only opened sound hands in first and second seat, usually at least 13 HCP. Therefore, they had to open light in 3rd and 4th seat to make up for the sound openers in 1st and 2nd seat because otherwise they might miss a game on occasion. |
PG| ***** 76 ***** |


nt||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, these days, most people like to get in the auction as early as possible, so we all tend to use the rule of 20 to determine if we have an opening hand. Therefore, there is not a need to open light in 3rd and 4th seat. So, I personally like to know that my partner has a "real" opener in 3rd and 4th seat, so I don't like to open light, as I am not afraid of our missing game. However, some people still open light and my problem with the light opener is that I now cannot judge as well how high to bid. That was a record discussion for a passed out hand, lol|
