^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|ally had a question. she thought that perhaps her 1@S bid is forcing.  This is a source of confusion among many players. New suits by responder are forcing. However, new suits  by opener are not forcing. If you have 18+ and partner responds, then opener knows she has game. In  that case, opener must make a forcing bid.  Forcing bids are jump shifts or reverses. Anything less than a jump shift or reverse limits your hand to 17 or so. ally is on the verge of a jump shift in spades, but her singleton heart is not good, so 1@S is ok.  2@S would also be acceptable.|
